requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall have LCD that displays numerical values derived from the data acquired at the analog outputs received from the pods.

issues.description: The term 'LCD' is ambiguous and differs from 'LCD screen' used in later requirements; it's unclear whether this refers to the LCD or the LCDScreen class.
issues.suggested_fix: Unify terminology and refer to a single display component (e.g., 'LCDScreen') consistently.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall allow pods to transfer vital data back to the PMS through 14-Pin connectors.

issues.description: The acronym 'PMS' is used here but elsewhere requirements refer to 'the system' or 'Patient Monitoring System'; this inconsistency may cause confusion.
issues.suggested_fix: Use the full system name 'Patient Monitoring System' or define and use the acronym consistently.

issues.description: Requirements do not specify how many 14-pin connectors are needed or whether they must be hot-swappable, etc.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify the number and physical characteristics of the 14-pin connectors and whether they support hot-swap.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall have a port for the pod that records pulse/pressure/oximeter/telemetry leads.

issues.description: No details on the number, type, or mapping of ports to pod types; location and identification of ports are undefined.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify for each pod type how many ports are required, their identification and physical mapping.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The LCD screen shall show the EGG strip in a green color (using hexadecimal color code: #00FF00).

issues.description: Typographical error: 'EGG strip' should be 'ECG strip', which mismatches the domain model class name.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall allow hospital to choose the language to display in, with the default being English.

issues.description: The mechanism for language selection and supported languages beyond default is not fully specified until REQ-3.3.15.1.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify UI controls for language selection and list all supported languages in this requirement.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall have a two-hour battery life.

issues.description: Battery life under what conditions (full load, idle, typical use)? Units are given but context is missing.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify test conditions for battery life (e.g., full monitoring load) and whether two hours is a minimum guaranteed or typical value.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system in one-minute intervals, shall send record updates to the Patient Records System database of the field data

issues.description: Unclear when the one-minute interval starts and whether initial data is sent immediately or after the first interval.
issues.suggested_fix: Define the exact timing semantics (e.g., send immediately upon first measurement, then every 60 seconds thereafter).

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall have a unique identifier code to identify each patient.

issues.description: It's unclear whether the identifier is managed per patient or per system session; 'each patient' implies a Patient entity that is not defined.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify that the Patient entity has an attribute 'uniqueIdentifierCode' and how it is generated and managed.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall not receive software updates when connected to a patient.

issues.description: The phrase 'connected to a patient' is undefined—does it refer to powering, data link, or physical attachment?
issues.suggested_fix: Define what 'connected to a patient' means and under what exact conditions update reception is disabled.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The patient-monitoring system's ethernet connection shall be capable of 100 Mbps while connected to the dock.

issues.description: Bandwidth is specified but no test procedure or margin (e.g., sustained vs. burst throughput) is defined.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify performance test criteria and whether 100 Mbps is a minimum sustained rate or a peak rate.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The system shall come with a user guide containing the following sections: How to setup the system during patient admission; How to use the system to monitor patient vitals after admission; How to use the system when transporting the patient.

issues.description: The content of each section is not specified, and the domain model does not represent sections within the UserGuide.
issues.suggested_fix: Define expected content for each section or model GuideSection entities in the domain.

domain_model_issues.description: Two classes represent display functionality ('LCD' for numerical values and 'LCDScreen' for color-coded data) causing redundancy.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Unify into a single Display class or clearly separate responsibilities and rename consistently.

domain_model_issues.description: No Patient class exists to model patient identity, yet requirements refer to patient-specific data and connections.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add a Patient class with attributes (e.g., uniqueIdentifierCode) and an association to PatientMonitoringSystem.

domain_model_issues.description: The unique identifier code is placed on the system rather than the Patient entity.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Move 'uniqueIdentifierCode' attribute to the Patient class.

domain_model_issues.description: Pod-specific classes exist but are not modeled as specializations of the Pod class.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Create generalization relationships from Pulse, Pressure, Oximeter, TelemetryLeads to Pod.

domain_model_issues.description: Ports exist but there is no link between Port and Pod to show which pod plugs into which port.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add an association between Port and Pod with appropriate multiplicities.

domain_model_issues.description: VitalsRecord is defined but not linked to the system for storing or displaying historical data.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add a composition from PatientMonitoringSystem to VitalsRecord with multiplicity reflecting 24-hour storage.

domain_model_issues.description: No associations exist from the system to RespiratoryWaveForm, O2SaturationWaveForm, or ECG despite display requirements.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Link PatientMonitoringSystem to these data classes to model data flow.

domain_model_issues.description: Local storage for last 24 hours of sensor data is implemented as a method but not modeled as a class.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Introduce a LocalDataCache (or similar) class to represent stored data.

domain_model_issues.description: No Language or enumeration exists to represent selectable languages (English, Spanish, French).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add a Language class or enum and associate it with PatientMonitoringSystem.

domain_model_issues.description: UserGuide is aggregated by PatientMonitoringSystem rather than composed under Documentation with the other guides.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Model UserGuide as a composition under Documentation alongside other guides.

domain_model_issues.description: Two separate classes exist without clear distinction: 'Dock' for LAN vs 'DockingStation' for power.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Clarify roles or merge into one class with separate behaviors or rename for clarity.

domain_model_issues.description: Bandwidth is modeled as a String rather than a numeric type, making performance calculations difficult.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Change 'bandwidth' attribute to a numeric type (e.g., integer in Mbps).

domain_model_issues.description: DockingStation is separate from ExternalDCPower without an association, obscuring power source mapping.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add an association showing DockingStation provides ExternalDCPower to the system.

domain_model_issues.description: Method is generic but requirements specify updates per vital type at one-minute intervals.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add parameters or separate methods for each vital type or define a DataType parameter.

domain_model_issues.description: This class has grown excessively large with many unrelated responsibilities (display, storage, power management, updates).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Refactor into smaller subsystems (e.g., DisplayManager, PowerManager, DataRecorder) to improve modularity.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement to display battery charge level or warn when battery is low
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall display the remaining battery charge level on the LCD and generate an audible and visual low-battery warning when the remaining battery life falls below 15 minutes.
missing_requirements.rationale: Without a battery status display and low-battery warning, clinicians may be unaware of impending power loss, risking interruption of patient monitoring.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement for automatic, seamless power switchover between battery and external DC power
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall automatically switch between internal battery power and external DC power without interrupting data acquisition or display, completing the switchover within 100 milliseconds of detecting the alternate power source.
missing_requirements.rationale: To ensure continuous monitoring during docking or undocking, power source transitions must be seamless and rapid, preventing data loss or system shutdown.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement to detect and report pod connection or disconnection events
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall detect when a pod is connected to or disconnected from any port and display a status notification on the LCD indicating the pod type and connection state; if a pod disconnects during monitoring, the system shall trigger an alarm.
missing_requirements.rationale: Clinicians need immediate feedback on pod connectivity to guarantee continuous vital data flow and respond quickly to sensor failures.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement for alarm acknowledgement or silencing controls
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall allow authorized hospital personnel to acknowledge and silence active alarms; silenced alarms shall remain suppressed for a configurable interval and automatically resume if the alarm condition persists beyond that interval.
missing_requirements.rationale: To reduce alarm fatigue and support workflow, users must be able to control alarms while ensuring persistent conditions are not ignored.

missing_requirements.description: No specific requirement for encrypting patient data at rest or in transit
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall encrypt all stored patient data using AES-256 and secure all network communications using TLS 1.2 or higher; it shall also verify data integrity on receipt.
missing_requirements.rationale: HIPAA Security Rule mandates encryption of protected health information to maintain confidentiality and integrity of patient data.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement for user authentication or role-based access control
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall require individual user authentication before granting access to patient data or configuration functions; access privileges shall be enforced based on predefined roles (e.g., nurse, technician, administrator).
missing_requirements.rationale: Preventing unauthorized access and modifications is essential for patient safety and HIPAA compliance.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement to maintain audit logs of user actions and system events
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall record an immutable audit log of user actions (logins, range definitions, alarm acknowledgements) and system events (power source changes, software updates) with timestamps and allow export of these logs for compliance review.
missing_requirements.rationale: Audit trails are required under HIPAA Security Rule to track access and changes for investigations and compliance verification.

missing_requirements.description: No specification of integration protocol or message format for Epic EMR and Central PMS
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall exchange data with the Epic EMR and the Central Patient-Monitoring System using the HL7 v2.x messaging standard over the hospital LAN and shall process message acknowledgments within 5 seconds.
missing_requirements.rationale: Defining a specific interoperability standard is necessary to ensure reliable and timely integration with external health record and monitoring systems.

missing_requirements.description: No requirements for sensor data sampling rates or display update frequencies
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall sample analog waveform data (ECG, respiratory, O2 saturation) at a minimum of 200 samples per second and update numerical vital displays (heart rate, blood pressure, O2 saturation, respiration rate) at least once per second.
missing_requirements.rationale: To provide accurate, real-time monitoring, sampling and display refresh rates must be specified and adhered to.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement to validate, persist, and reload custom vital ranges or revert to defaults
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall validate that each defined vital range has a lower bound less than its upper bound, persist custom ranges to non-volatile memory, and load them at startup; if no custom ranges exist, default manufacturer ranges shall apply.
missing_requirements.rationale: Ensuring range definitions are valid, retained across power cycles, and default values are available prevents configuration errors and maintains monitoring integrity.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement for a startup self-test or system health check
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: Upon power-up, the system shall perform a self-test of critical components (pods, battery, Ethernet connection, LCD) and display a system health summary on the LCD; if any test fails, the system shall trigger an alarm and prevent monitoring until the fault is resolved.
missing_requirements.rationale: A built-in self-test ensures hardware and software readiness before patient monitoring begins, reducing risk of undetected failures.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement to confirm docking station connection status to the user
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: When the system is placed on the docking station, the system shall display a confirmation message on the LCD indicating successful docking and external DC power availability.
missing_requirements.rationale: User feedback on successful docking helps verify that external power is available and the device is correctly seated for charging and LAN connectivity.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The system shall connect to the hospital LAN via an Ethernet connection when attached to the dock.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement:
Augment the requirement with management and verification details. For example:
"REQ-3.1.1 [Priority: High; Source: Network Team; Version: 1.0]
Rationale: To ensure reliable, real-time data flow.
The system shall connect to the hospital LAN via an Ethernet connection when attached to the dock.
Acceptance Criteria:
  – Upon docking, establish a LAN link within 5 seconds;
  – Verify 100 Mbps throughput.
Dependencies: REQ-3.7.4; Status: Draft."
requirement_completeness.rationale: Adding these fields ensures traceability, testability and clear project management.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The system shall have LCD that displays numerical values derived from the data acquired at the analog outputs received from the pods.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement:
Include missing management/test fields. E.g.:
"REQ-3.1.2 [Priority: Medium; Source: UX Team; Version: 1.0]
Rationale: Ensure clinicians can read vital signs immediately.
The system shall have an LCD that displays numerical values derived from the data acquired at the analog outputs received from the pods.
Acceptance Criteria:
  – Values update at least once per second;
  – Contrast and font size meet accessibility standards.
Dependencies: REQ-3.1.3; Status: Draft."
requirement_completeness.rationale: Explicit acceptance criteria and metadata enable proper validation and tracking.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The system shall allow pods to transfer vital data back to the PMS through 14-Pin connectors.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement:
Extend with metadata and test conditions. E.g.:
"REQ-3.1.3 [Priority: High; Source: Hardware Team; Version: 1.0]
Rationale: Support modular pod design.
The system shall allow pods to transfer vital data back to the PMS through 14-Pin connectors.
Acceptance Criteria:
  – Signal integrity meets IEEE-rated thresholds;
  – All pod types recognized within 2 s of connection.
Dependencies: REQ-3.1.3.1–.4; Status: Draft."
requirement_completeness.rationale: Clear dependencies and acceptance criteria prevent integration issues.
